## Domain Expertise Gate

The following categories require a human review pause before implementation begins. Automatic execution is not permitted.

| Category | Examples |
|---|---|
| Safety validation | Print parameter limits, thermal bounds, structural tolerances |
| Physical testing | Layer adhesion, support removal, dimensional accuracy |
| Hardware validation | Printer capability assumptions, nozzle wear, bed adhesion |
| Parameter tuning | Default values for speed, temperature, retraction |
| Business decisions | Pricing, launch timing, access control policy |
| Architecture decisions | Changes to approved structures in `frontend-architecture.mdc` |
| Launch approval | Any story gating a production deployment |

When a story falls into a gate category:

1. Name the category.
2. List assumptions the implementation would rely on.
3. List the risks if those assumptions are wrong.
4. Stop. Do not write code.

---

## Commit Policy

Every completed story produces exactly one recommended commit message. Milestone-level commits are not generated.

### Format

```
<type>(s-x.y): short imperative description
```

### Rules

- **Choose the type that best describes the story's output:**

  | Type | Use when the story… |
  |---|---|
  | `feat` | Delivers user-visible behavior — a rendered page, an interactive input, a working button |
  | `fix` | Corrects a defect in a previously delivered story |
  | `test` | Adds or updates tests without changing production code |
  | `chore` | Scaffolds infrastructure, defines types, configures build tooling — no user-visible change |
  | `docs` | Updates documentation only |

- Scope is always the story ID: `s-x.y`
- Verb is imperative: `implement`, `add`, `scaffold`, `wire`, `generate`, `fix`
- Total length is under 72 characters

### Examples

```
feat(s-3.2): implement configure form inputs
feat(s-2.2): implement layered parameter resolver
feat(s-2.3): implement safety guardrail validator
chore(s-1.1): scaffold vite project and test tooling
chore(s-2.1): define engine-internal types
fix(s-3.4): correct slug construction for 0.6mm nozzle
```

The developer commits. This rule recommends. Do not run `git commit` automatically.

